title: Britain at Bay
dc:creator: U.S. Army Heritage and Education Center
description: In this lecture, Dr. Alan Allport of Syracuse University, discusses World War II’s critical first years and how the United Kingdom’s strategic and political decisions impacted the outcome of the war.
